# Data Exploration Notebook

This notebook explores the audio samples collected from Splice.com.

## Setup

```python
import sys
from pathlib import Path
sys.path.insert(0, str(Path.cwd().parent))

from src.data.audio_loader import AudioLoader
from src.utils.audio_utils import AudioUtils
from src.config import config
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
```

## Load Data

```python
# Initialize loader
loader = AudioLoader()

# Load all samples
samples = loader.load_all_samples()

# Display statistics
for category, audio_list in samples.items():
    print(f"{category}: {len(audio_list)} samples")
```

## Load Metadata

```python
# Load metadata CSV
metadata = loader.load_metadata()
metadata.head()
```

## Visualize Audio

```python
# Plot waveform for a sample
if samples:
    category = list(samples.keys())[
    0
]
    audio, filename = samples[category
][
    0
]
    
    audio_utils = AudioUtils()
    audio_utils.plot_waveform(audio, config.SAMPLE_RATE, title=f"Waveform - {filename}")
    audio_utils.plot_spectrogram(audio, config.SAMPLE_RATE, title=f"Spectrogram - {filename}")
```

## Category Distribution

```python
# Plot category distribution
if not metadata.empty:
    category_counts = metadata['category'
].value_counts()
    category_counts.plot(kind='bar', title='Category Distribution')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.show()
